headline: Has Coca Cola’s Recent Run Left Much Upside at Around $70 a Share?
summary: Wondering if Coca Cola is still a buy at around $70 a share, or if most of the upside has already been priced in? This article will unpack whether the current tag makes sense for a slow and steady compounder like KO. The stock has cooled slightly in the short term, down about 0.2% over the last week and 1.1% over the last month, but is still up roughly 13.8% year to date and 15.8% over the past year, which is solid for a mature consumer staple.
